# 2p_sync — host. Spawns near client (foundry FFA lanes 16/24 are
# adjacent), then jets straight up + comes back down. Pairs with
# 2p_sync.client.shot which sits still and observes.
#
# What we test:
#   - Host's view of HOST mech (predicted, smooth) vs client's view
#     of HOST mech (snapshot-driven via P03 interp ring).
#   - Both views capture the same world ticks so a side-by-side
#     visual diff is meaningful (camera offsets differ but world
#     positions of the host's mech should agree).
#   - At each shot tick, the host's pelvis pos in BOTH logs should
#     be within ~10 px of each other (one snapshot interval of motion
#     at jet speed).

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/sync_host
network host 24061
name HostA

# Match starts ~tick 130 (after 1 s countdown). Skip the first
# few ticks so spawn settles, then do a clean jet sequence.
at 200 press jet
at 280 release jet
# Land + recover.
at 330 press jet
at 360 release jet

at 200 shot pre_jet
at 240 shot mid_jet_up
at 280 shot peak
at 320 shot falling
at 360 shot mid_jet_down
at 400 shot landed
at 700 shot after
at 750 end
